{"article_id":"shhinLnlG7FJBvtC","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Brett Kavanaugh was sworn in as the 114th Supreme Court justice in a private ceremony Saturday","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"just hours after the Senate voted to confirm him ,","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"solidifying conservative control of the highest court in the land for years to come","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"and ending a bitter battle over his nomination .","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"The confirmation delivered a major win to President Donald Trump ,","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"who defended his embattled nominee","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"when sexual assault accusations were leveled against him .","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"Kavanaugh has denied the accusations .","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"Trump ,","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"speaking at a rally in Topeka , Kansas ,","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"called it a `` truly historic night '' and a `` tremendous victory . ''","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"He added :","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"`` What he and his wonderful family endured at the hands of Democrats is unthinkable . ''","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"Kavanaugh 's confirmation was not just a chance","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"for Republicans","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"to shift the court to the right for what could be decades .","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"It was also a test","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"of how public officials responded to the raw emotions","depth":13},{"id":19,"text":"unleashed by the # MeToo movement amid accusations from Christine Blasey Ford","depth":14},{"id":20,"text":"that Kavanaugh had sexually assaulted her","depth":15},{"id":21,"text":"when they were teens .","depth":15},{"id":22,"text":"He said","depth":13},{"id":23,"text":"the incident never happened .","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"That controversy will likely be scrutinized even further with the Nov. 6 midterm elections a month away ,","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"giving Democrats have a chance","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"to take control of one or more chambers of Congress .","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"The anger among Kavanaugh 's critics was evident on the steps of the Capitol","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"where hundreds of protesters ,","depth":14},{"id":29,"text":"many dressed in black garb ,","depth":14},{"id":30,"text":"had gathered on the steps","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"holding signs","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"and chanting .","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"A cordon of police officers stood in front of the doors .","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"Capitol Police said","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"they arrested 164 people from among the hundreds of protestors","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"who had gathered .","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"Most , some 150 , were arrested on the Capitol 's east side .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"The final Senate vote was 50-48 .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"Sen. Joe Manchin was the only Democrat","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"to break ranks","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"and vote in favor of him .","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"Trump congratulated Kavanaugh on Twitter","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"and called him a `` great nominee . ''","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"He signed Kavanaugh 's commission to the Supreme Court aboard Air Force One","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"so he could get to work immediately on the court .","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"Shortly after , Kavanaugh ,","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"accompanied by his family ,","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"was sworn in by Chief Justice John Roberts Jr. and retired Justice Anthony Kennedy ,","depth":14},{"id":49,"text":"who Kavanaugh is replacing ,","depth":14},{"id":50,"text":"during a private ceremony at the Supreme Court .","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"The 6 p.m. ceremony marks the beginning of his lifetime appointment .","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"For weeks , Kavanaugh 's future had hung in the balance during hours of hearings , FBI investigations into the sexual assault allegations .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"The remarkable and ugly set of twists and turns","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"that ended with Saturday 's vote .","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"Kavanaugh 's path to confirmation became clear Friday afternoon","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"when Sen. Susan Collins , R-Maine ,","depth":14},{"id":57,"text":"who had been on the fence for months ,","depth":14},{"id":58,"text":"announced her support in a 45-minute speech on the Senate floor .","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"`` It is","depth":15},{"id":60,"text":"when passions are most inflamed","depth":16},{"id":61,"text":"that fairness is most in jeopardy , ''","depth":16},{"id":62,"text":"she said .","depth":14},{"id":63,"text":"`` I will vote to confirm Judge Kavanaugh . ''","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"More :","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"Kavanaugh fight caused bitterness ,","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"but senators say","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"they 'll be friends again - one day","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"More :","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"Protesters disrupt final vote","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"to confirm Brett Kavanaugh as a Supreme Court justice","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"More :","depth":15},{"id":72,"text":"'Very , very difficult vote ' :","depth":15},{"id":73,"text":"The wavering senators","depth":15},{"id":74,"text":"who decided","depth":16},{"id":75,"text":"whether Brett Kavanaugh joins the Supreme Court","depth":16},{"id":76,"text":"Sen. Lisa Murkowski of Alaska was the only Republican against Kavanaugh 's appointment .","depth":14},{"id":77,"text":"She voted as \" present \" as a collegial gesture for her Republican colleague Sen. Steve Daines ,","depth":16},{"id":78,"text":"who supports Kavanaugh","depth":17},{"id":79,"text":"but is attending his daughter 's wedding Saturday .","depth":17},{"id":80,"text":"The gesture did not affect the outcome of the final vote","depth":16},{"id":81,"text":"but changed the tally to 50-48 in favor of Kavanaugh 's confirmation .","depth":16},{"id":82,"text":"Kavanaugh 's confirmation was marked by mudslinging from both sides","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"that divided the nation even deeper ,","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"but there was one thing","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"both Democrats and Republicans agreed one :","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"It was an ugly process","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"that should n't be repeated .","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"Majority Leader Mitch McConnell and Minority Leader Chuck Schumer offered remarks","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"moments before the final votes were cast .","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"Schumer ,","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"speaking first ,","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"said","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"the nomination from start to finish `` has been one of the saddest moments in the history of the Senate . '' `` Truly , Judge Kavanaugh 's confirmation is a low moment for the Senate , for the court and for the country , ''","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"McConnell seemed to agree .","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"He said","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"Kavanaugh ' s record was one","depth":14},{"id":98,"text":"that `` speaks for itself ''","depth":14},{"id":99,"text":"and the ugly process showed his patience and humility .","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"McConnell said","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"the bitterness \" fanned the flames \" of partisan divisions throughout the country .","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"As the votes were cast ,","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"many senators sat silently","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"with their hands across their laps .","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"There were no cheers or applause at the conclusion .","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"Some senators did hug or pat one another on the back .","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"The atmosphere outside the Capitol differed .","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"Protesters held signs","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"reading `` Kava Nope '' and `` Shame , Collins , ''","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"the latter a reference to the announcement by Collins","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"that she planned to vote in support of the controversial Kavanaugh .","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"Many of the protesters said","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"they felt powerless","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"but vowed","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"that next month 's midterms would change that .","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"Before Vice President Mike Pence called for the first vote ,","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"protesters in the Senate angrily began yelling","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"and were dragged out of the chamber by police .","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"\" I do not consent , \" a woman could be heard screaming","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"more than a minute after she was taken away .","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"Pence ,","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"who is also president of the Senate ,","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"had to ask the sergeant at arms to restore order in the gallery at least a half dozen times .","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"Both Republicans and Democrats expect the Kavanaugh decision to be a central theme in the midterm elections .","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"Trump 's promise during his 2016 campaign","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"to put conservatives on the Supreme Court","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"reinforced his support among Republicans .","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"In 2018 , Democrats hope to ride to a `` blue wave '' of anger over Trump and Kavanaugh","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"that could flip control of Congress .","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"But Republicans believe","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"the battle over Kavanaugh will help energize their voters , too .","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"Democrats are seen as having a solid chance","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"to captured the House ,","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"fueled in part by women voters","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"who are upset over Kavanaugh","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"and dislike Trump .","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"But taking over the Senate is likely to be a lot tougher .","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"Democrats are defending multiple seats in states","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"Trump easily carried in that chamber .","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"In those states , the Kavanaugh vote could help Republicans .","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"More :","depth":7},{"id":142,"text":"A reminder on where Brett Kavanaugh stands on controversial issues","depth":7},{"id":143,"text":"More :","depth":8},{"id":144,"text":"$ 3 million","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"raised for Sen. Susan Collins ' opponent amid outcry on Kavanaugh vote","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"Opinion :","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"Rejuvenated Republicans rediscover unity in litmus-test","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"Brett Kavanaugh confirmation fight","depth":4},{"id":149,"text":"Trump stepped into the political battle over the confirmation","depth":8},{"id":150,"text":"as allegations piled up against Kavanaugh .","depth":8},{"id":151,"text":"White House aides had initially taken a more cautious approach ,","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"advising the president to tread carefully around a controversy","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"that may still sour suburban women and independent voters .","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"But in recent days Trump changed tack ,","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"viewing an outcry over the last-minute allegations of sexual assault against Kavanaugh as a way","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"to drive turnout .","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"At a Minnesota rally on Thursday , Trump launched his latest rhetorical attack on the political storm","depth":9},{"id":158,"text":"surrounding Kavanaugh 's confirmation","depth":9},{"id":159,"text":"by saying","depth":10},{"id":160,"text":"Democrats were `` trying to destroy '' the Court of Appeals judge","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"and predicting","depth":10},{"id":162,"text":"they would pay a price in the November elections .","depth":10},{"id":163,"text":"`` Their rage-fueled resistance is starting to backfire , ''","depth":9},{"id":164,"text":"Trump told the audience ,","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"which responded with chants of Kavanaugh 's name .","depth":10},{"id":166,"text":"`` These people are loco . ''","depth":8},{"id":167,"text":"Kavanaugh ' s nomination always was destined to become a partisan battleground","depth":6},{"id":168,"text":"because of the justice","depth":8},{"id":169,"text":"he was picked","depth":9},{"id":170,"text":"to replace :","depth":9},{"id":171,"text":"Anthony Kennedy , the Supreme Court ' s swing vote ,","depth":9},{"id":172,"text":"who had sided with his liberal colleagues on issues such as abortion , affirmative action and gay rights .","depth":9},{"id":173,"text":"Kennedy , 81 , retired after three decades in the middle of the court ' s ideological battles .","depth":8},{"id":174,"text":"Contributing : Richard Wolf , Eliza Collins , Maureen Groppe , John Fritze , David Jackson , Associated Press","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":349,"left":0,"right":348,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":348,"left":347,"right":174,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":347,"left":321,"right":346,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":321,"left":297,"right":320,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":297,"left":255,"right":296,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":255,"left":187,"right":254,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":187,"left":178,"right":186,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":176,"right":177,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":186,"left":181,"right"